children.subject: I would phase 2 61B or the breadth. Data 8 tends to fill up really quickly, and you'll want a good lab time for 16B. How fast the breadth fills up depends on which breadth it is, so I'd suggest checking out the enrollment graphs on https://www.berkeleytime.com/. In general, 61B is safe to phase 2, and I'd wager this to still be true even given the budget cuts.

history.content: I'm a freshman intended CS and Data science minor. I'm looking to take 61B, 16B, a breadth and data 8 next sem. I can declare after 61B so even though it seems like an easier class to phase 2, I don't know if I should take that risk given the fewer seats this semester. 16B would be good finish next semester after 16a this semester. Data 8 seems to fill up fast, but I imagine that it would be easiest to just move to another semester without influencing much later. Breadth fills up fairly fast based on last time it was offered (60% after phase 1 last year). Which is the best option to phase 2?
history.subject: Which class to phase 2?
